-- Mozambique Gives The Go-Ahead for Dam on Zambezi River, O Pais Reports
-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 2010-12-24T09:41:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-24/mozambique-gives-the-go-ahead-for-dam-on-zambezi-river-o-pais-reports.html
Mozambique’s government gave the go-
ahead for work to start on the $2.4 billion Mpanda Nkuwa
hydroelectric plant on the Zambezi River, O Pais reported.  The power station will be build by Hidroelectrica de Mpanda
Nkuwa, which includes Electricidade de Mocambique, Brazil’s
Camargo Correa SA and Mozambique’s Insitec SGPS SA, the Maputo-
based newspaper said, citing Egidio Leite, the chief executive
officer of the Hidroelectrica. The plant will have a capacity of
1,500 megawatts.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Fred Katerere  in Maputo at  fkaterere@bloomberg.net 
or.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 